projects.projectName: LOC8TE: A Velocity Renovation and Google API as Geofencing Professional Locator & Virtual Space
projects.projectShortDesc: An android application aimed at connecting individuals with nearby professionals and facilitating communication between them. It enables professionals to build relationships and establish trust with clients by showcasing their profiles, which include information such as ratings, experiences, skills, and more. Moreover, clients can view the profiles of the professionals and initiate communication once a connection is established. Lastly, there is a feature which lets professionals organize events so that other professionals and clients can participate in it.

projects.projectName: EmoBot: A Depression Prevention Android App using Machine Learning.
projects.projectShortDesc: EmoBot is a one-of-a-kind android application designed to help you apply effective strategies for preventing incoming depression. EmoBot draws upon the principles and techniques of Cognitive Behavior Therapy (CBT), one of the most effective and scientifically-supported methods of psychotherapy. With four integrated tools, EmoBot helps you to engage in mood-enhancing activities, identify and change unhealthy thinking, rate and chart mood and hobbies across time, and give someone that will listen and talk about their problem.

projects.projectName: Liwanag: Emotion Recognition Using Facial Expression for the Visually Impaired
projects.projectShortDesc: Liwanag is an android mobile application that gives the visually impaired an access to non-verbal communication specifically facial expression by determining the emotion presented on the face of the person whom the visually impaired is talking to with the use of the rear camera of the phone.

projects.projectName: FIREph: Budget Planner Application using Regression Algorithms
projects.projectShortDesc: FirePH is a financial management tool that uses regression and time-series forecasting algorithms to help users track and forecast their expenses. The application includes modules for inserting transactions, retrieving and displaying transactions, forecasting transactions, generating reports, managing expenses, and offering credential verification. The application serves to help users become more aware of their expenditures and identify areas where they can reduce their spending.

projects.projectName: Codex Learning: A Game-Based Intelligent Tutoring System using Expert-Based Modeling to Measure the Skills and Knowledge of Novice Programmers in Java Programming.
projects.projectShortDesc: A retro styled gamified desktop application that teaches the Fundamentals of Java Programming Language (JPL). The application collects the value of the skills and knowledge of novice programmers through theoretical -Question and Answer- and practical -Place the block- activities. This application is built to inspire and teach novice programmers to know the basics and proper placement of code components of JPL.

projects.projectName: License Plate Recognition with Violation Checker Using Yolo and Tesseract-CNN Algorithm
projects.projectShortDesc: A web based application that uses YOLO and Tesseract-CNN algorithms to detect license plate numbers through video feeds. This mainly benefits drivers and traffic officials. An authorized administrator can perform CRUD operations on car and violation data. Additionally, there is a violation checker that allows vehicle owners to input their engine number. Selected traffic officals can receive SMS notifications about detected hot plates and related information, while vehicle owners can receive notifications if they have been issued a violation.

projects.projectName: (B.M.A) Android/iOS Budget Monitoring Application using Predictive Analytics
projects.projectShortDesc: BMA is a mobile application designed to help users monitor their budget and give them a glimpse of what could be their future expenditure with the help of AI. It features a predictive AI that gives the user an estimate of what could be their future expense based on the user's past data. It also has an OCR function to make it easier for the users to input their expense by taking a picture of receipts and it goes directly to our database which the user can also see inside the App.

projects.projectName: Grocery Dash: A Mobile-based Grocery Shopping Assistant with the Application of the Hamiltonian Path Problem of Graph Theory
projects.projectShortDesc: An android application that allows on-site grocery shoppers to list their desired items, view the total price, check for item suggestions, and follow a generated sub-optimal path for gathering all of their grocery needs. Developed using Java and Google Firebase, Grocery Dash incorporates various algorithms for pathfinding, graph traversal, and shortest path problems to help its users navigate the grocery store.

projects.projectName: An Android Application for Symptom Awareness of Measles, Mumps, and Rubella with Digital Rash Image Detection
projects.projectShortDesc: SKIP is an android application that provides information to users about the importance of MMR vaccine. Information such as symptoms and incubation period of diseases like measles, mumps, and rubella will be available to users. The application also provides a list of locations as well as the contact information of hospitals and clinics that provide the MMR vaccine. An additional feature of the application is to classify whether the skin is healthy or not.

projects.projectName: Facial Recognition Attendance System Using Line Detection Algorithm
projects.projectShortDesc: An attendance system that provides a touch-less alternative to other personnel monitoring methods, especially to manual methods still used today. This is done by utilizing object detection and facial recognition models, in conjunction with a line detection algorithm to create a system whose operation is triggered by a user's proximity to the camera, while also being able to recognize users despite the presence of face masks. A web-based application is also created to facilitate user/admin functionalities.
